{"questionId":"9074780","questionHtml":"<p>A ray of white light is normally incident on a thin layer of oil on water. The refractive index of oil is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> and the refractive index of water is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a68c2c5e250a0b984f0c474934dfa2493830fb9c.png\"></p>\n<p>The wavelength of violet light in air is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>v</mtext></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>What is the minimum thickness of the thin layer of oil so that the colour of the reflected light is violet?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>v</mtext></msub><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>v</mtext></msub></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>v</mtext></msub><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>λ</mi><mtext>v</mtext></msub><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074780","referenceCode":"22N.1.HL.TZ0.27","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A ray of white light is normally incident on a thin layer of oil on water. The refractive index of oil is 32 and the refractive index of water is 43. The wavelength of violet light","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"27","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.3 – Interference","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}